    "description": "Reliance Industries Consulting Pvt Ltd invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Quality Control Engineer at our Srinagar location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Reliance Industries Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nReliance Industries Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Flexible working hours\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Reliance Industries Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
